                                    <a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#faq-accordion" href="#third-collapse" aria-controls="third-collapse">
                                        Resume & Editor
                                    </a>
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div id="third-collapse" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="third-question">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p id="pro-features">
                                      <strong>Which are the pro/paid features that I'm using and how can I remove them?</strong>
                                      ​You can go to the <a href="https://app.enhancv.com/plans" target="_blank">Plans</a> page and click on 'Remove Premium Features'.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="logo-removal">
                                      <strong>Can I remove your logo from the bottom of the resume page?</strong>
                                      Yes :) Choose the Layout option from the sidebar and switch the 'Remove Logo' option. Have in mind that this is a Pro feature.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-rearrangement">
                                      <strong>Can I rearrange the sections and the items in them?</strong>
                                      Yes. You can drag the items within a section to reorder them. To move entire sections (e.g. Experience, Education) go to 'Rearrange/Edit' in the sidebar. The platform automatically calculates how to position entries across pages, so sometimes a single section could be spread across multiple pages.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="toggle-fields">
                                      <strong>How can I hide the date, location or link in a section item?</strong>
                                      Just click the section item you want to change, then on the wheel icon above it. There you'll see all the show/hide options.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-history">
                                      <strong>Can I revert an unwanted change I made to my resume?</strong>
                                      Yes, you can. We keep a history of the last actions you made.
                                      You can use it by clicking the Undo and Redo buttons which are located in the upper part of the sidebar. Changes made in previous browser sessions cannot be reverted unfortunately.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-fontsize">
                                      <strong>Can I change the font size of the texts and headings in the resume?</strong>
                                      Unfortunately, we don't support that. We are working on a new condensed layout, however, that will be released soon!
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-resizing">
                                      <strong>Can I resize the different sections and items in them?</strong>
                                      Unfortunately, we don't support that. We are working on a new condensed layout, however, that will be released soon!
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-templates">
                                      <strong>Do you have predefined templates with different styles?</strong>
                                      Not for now, but we give you a complete freedom of how you arrange your sections, which fields are visible, what colors and fonts you choose as well as what icons you put.
                                      Different resume layouts including a condensed variant (one that fits more text on one page) are coming soon.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="multiple-resumes">
                                      <strong>Can I have multiple resumes in one account?</strong>
                                      Yes you can. For the Free plan you can have 2 different resumes in your dashboard. If you need more than 2 you'll have to use one of our paid plans!
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-export">
                                      <strong>Can I export my resume as a MS Word document or HTML code?</strong>
                                      No. We've picked PDF because it is the only one that guarantees your resume will always look good across devices. It is also a format that everyone accepts!
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-missing-info">
                                      <strong>Why is my resume shortened after choosing the Free plan to download it?</strong>
                                      You were probably using Pro features and in order to download without upgrading you have to hide/remove those. You most definitely clicked on 'Remove Premium Features'.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-single-date">
                                      <strong>How do I leave a single date and not a period?</strong>
                                      Sure. Just leave the second date (the 'to' date) empty.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="certificate-images">
                                      <strong>How can I upload an image for each of my certificates?</strong>
                                      We don't have that functionality. It is a little hack, but you can use the Books section for that ;)
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="other-problem">
                                      <strong>I am experiencing other problems. What do I do?</strong>
                                      If you don't have any unsaved changes, try to refresh the page a couple of times.
                                      <br>
                                      <br>
                                      If this doesn't help, please get in touch with us and we'll help ASAP (preferably through the Chat button in the bottom-right corner).
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
